      <h2 class="intro-text text-center">
          Tasty Ramen In Houston <strong>(UPDATE)</strong>
      </h2>
      <hr>
      <p class="lead">It's been awhile since I've talked about one of my favorite foods (Ramen) and now there's good reason to do so again. <%= link_to "Ramen Tatsuya", "http://ramen-tatsuya.com/" %>, the amazing Ramen chain from Austin has just opened their first shop in Houston! </p>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
      <h3>Ramen Tatsuya in Houston</h3>
      <p>We had the privilege of trying it out and it does not disappoint. The shop is located off of Westheimer in the Montrose area at <%= link_to "1722 California Street", "https://www.google.com/maps/place/1722+California+St,+Houston,+TX+77006/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x8640c09ea4f455d5:0x2e3935ef4e4eeb2f?sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwifwLfc4ZTSAhVMzVQKHXrQBggQ8gEIGTAA" %>. It appears that the secret is already out, however, because you can expect lines out the door at peak meal times.  If you're not a fan of waiting to be seated, I recommend you try it at an off-time.</p>
      <p>We have many excellent selections of Ramen around town now.  I feel like Houston has finally made it with the Ramen scene. Other shops have great noodles, or great broth, or great ajitama, but I would say Tatsuya is the only one I've been to so far that has the full package.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-1"></div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-5">
      <%= image_tag @blog.image_link("tatsuya_entrance"), class: "img img-responsive img-rounded" %>
    </div>
  </div><!-- end of row -->
</div>
<div class="box text-justify">
