      <h4>Best all-around Ramen in Houston</h4>
      <p>My Ramen journey started in Austin at Ramen Tatsuya and now it has come full circle. Their location here in Houston is larger than the shop I've been to in Austin, but the decorations are similar and give me the idea that they were going for hipster meets Japanese countryside.  It's the Japanese equivalent of going to La Madeline and spray painting graffiti on the wall.</p>
      <p>We're here for Ramen, not for ambiance though.  Tatsuya is officially my favorite Ramen in Houston now.  The broth was a tad more salty than I remember from Austin, but not terribly so and the flavor was excellent. The noodles were nice and firm. The meat wasn't too fatty and had a smokey flavor. The ajitama was well marinated and the egg yolk was perfectly soft boiled.</p>
